<p>
If you’re curious about the various types of reports that have been submitted, take a look at our community search.  This functionality anyone to quickly search report descriptions for a particular topic of interest.  For example, if you’re interested in algae or construction, type it in the box and we’ll filter down the number of reports that best match your criteria.  Keep in mind that you can also search with hashtags.

</p>


<p>
1. Go to <a href="https://waterreporter.org" target="_blank">WaterReporter.org</a> and click <a href="https://waterreporter.org/search" target="_blank">Search Community</a>

<p>
2. Enter a word or phrase that you’re interested in.  
</p>

<p>
3. Click enter or search.    
</p>

<p>
4. Remember that adding a hashtag or clicking on a hashtag will run a full search for the variable you’re interested in.
</p>

